reviews.review_text: Wow, an ear opener... ...for a '95 show. So in reading the reviews left on the other available copies of this show many declared it either the worst/among the worst in of course what has to be considered an awful year for the GD and those that love them. But I couldn't tell by my ears that this was that awful a show. Did they set the house on fire? Well, yes, if you listen to the audience reaction to most songs, they certainly sound like they enjoyed it and I feel that I would have, too, had I been in the building. A long jammy Stranger, a longer & jammier Sugaree, a Minglewood that I actually enjoyed the performance of, not necessarily a fan of, a Ramble that Jerry actually sounded really excited about playing and the audience responding in kind, a always welcomed BT Wind. 50 minutes, they've done worse. Pre-Drumz was excellent to these ears and then one of the most unique/quickest versions of Stella Blue but yet with a full 2 minutes of Jerry after the vocals to end the song . This AUD is excellent imho.
